'''K'ril Tsutsaroth''' (pronounced {{IPAc-en|,|k|r|I|l|_|'|t|V|d|z|i:|r|Q|T}} {{respell|KRILL|_|TUTT|zee|roth}}{{CiteGeneral|url=http://services.runescape.com/m=rswiki/en/Pronunciation_Guide|title=Pronunciation Guide|accessdate=2022-4-21|author=Jagex|archiveurl=https://chisel.weirdgloop.org/oldwiki/archive1/services.runescape.com/m%3drswiki/en/Pronunciation_Guide.html|archivedate=2016-07-31}}) is the leader of [[Zamorak]]'s forces in the [[God Wars Dungeon]]. 

He is located in [[Zamorak's Fortress]], which requires 70 [[Hitpoints]] to cross the river to access. To gain access to his chamber, players must use an [[ecumenical key]] or have slain 40<ref>35 for hard, 30 for elite, 25 for master and 15 kills for grandmaster for those who have unlocked the respective combat achievement tiers</ref> Zamorakians throughout the dungeon.

He is typically killed on a [[Slayer task]] - K'ril Tsutsaroth is classified as a [[greater demon]], and thus killing him counts towards any greater demon Slayer task and allows a player to take advantage of the damage boosting effects of a [[Black mask]] or [[Slayer helmet]]. As a demon, he is also susceptible to [[demonbane weapon]]s and [[demonbane spells|spells]].

