==Fight overview==
{{Main|K'ril Tsutsaroth/Strategies}}
[[File:Fighting K'ril Tsutsaroth.png|thumb|300px|A group of players fighting K'ril Tsutsaroth and his bodyguards.]]
Like other God Wars Dungeon bosses, K'ril roams around a rectangular room with his bodyguards until a player enters, attacking them on sight. He attacks with melee and magic, and if his target is praying [[Protect from Melee]], he can use a devastating melee special attack that hits through prayer. The melee attack has a maximum hit of 46, the magic attack hits from 10-30{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1055016564595011585|date=24 October 2018|archiveurl=https://archive.is/z0Y5o|archivedate=26 May 2020|quote=Zilyana has a 10-20 attack and K'ril has a 10-30 attack.}} and the special attack hits from 35-49{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1247599267910467584|date=7 April 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/RSH4O|archivedate=26 May 2020|quote=Its damage is random, 35-49 inclusive, even distribution across those numbers.}}, as well as drains half of the player's current prayer points, rounded down. The relative occurrences of the attacks are 2/3 for melee and 1/3 for magic. Barring a complex mechanic, K'ril will use his special on 1 in every 9 hits instead of a melee attack, which gives it an incidence of 2/27 in total.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1247602346496004096|date=7 April 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/CFZMo|archivedate=26 May 2020|quote=The melee one looks more like a 2/3 to me, from the code, but the enraged attack would be part of that too, so it'd be less than 2/3 in practice.}}
If all players leave, his health and stats will be reset.

